                  <msItem>
                     <p> OXFORD (All Saints). <persName>
                           <forename>Simon</forename>, the prior</persName>, and 
               <orgName key="org_109039">convent of St. Frideswide</orgName>, grant to
               <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Padi</surname>
                        </persName> and his heirs the land which was
               Tholomei's in the <placeName key="place_109419">parish of All Saints</placeName>, situated between the land of
               <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> the miller</persName> and the cemetery of All Saints, at an
               annual rent of 4s. For this grant the said John gave 3 marks of silver. 
               Witness. <persName>
                           <forename>Philip</forename> the <surname>miller</surname>
                        </persName>. 
               (Simon, prior, <origDate notBefore="1210" notAfter="1227">1210-1227</origDate>.) 
                <!--[Wigram no. 380] -->  
               </p>
